these really, really well.

00:00:45.250 --> 00:00:46.835 align:middle line:90%
And how you wash leeks--

00:00:46.835 --> 00:00:48.270 align:middle line:90%
I'll just grab a knife actually.

00:00:48.270 --> 00:00:51.170 align:middle line:90%


00:00:51.170 --> 00:00:53.400 align:middle line:84%
How you wash leeks
is you cut down--

00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:54.900 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people
take away the green.

00:00:54.900 --> 00:00:55.700 align:middle line:90%
We need the green.

00:00:55.700 --> 00:00:59.270 align:middle line:84%
The green's the flavor,
lots of flavor in the green.

00:00:59.270 --> 00:01:02.400 align:middle line:84%
Just going to cut down
in here, and we're just

00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:08.355 align:middle line:84%
going to get the dirt that's
wrapped around each leaf,

00:01:08.355 --> 00:01:09.155 align:middle line:90%
really simply.

00:01:09.155 --> 00:01:14.648 align:middle line:90%


00:01:14.648 --> 00:01:16.190 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes you don't
have to cut them,

00:01:16.190 --> 00:01:18.030 align:middle line:84%
